#
# Request samples can be executed:
#
# a.) In Visual Studio Code with the HTTP Client Plugin
#     See: https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=mkloubert.vscode-http-client
#
# b.) In IntelliJ with the HTTP Client Plugin
#     See: https://www.jetbrains.com/help/idea/http-client-in-product-code-editor.html
#


### Valid JSON Lines stream — each line is validated against itemSchema, should work

POST http://localhost:2000/documents
Content-Type: application/jsonl

{"id": "1", "title": "First"}
{"id": "2", "title": "Second"}

### Invalid stream — the second item misses the required "title", should fail

POST http://localhost:2000/documents
Content-Type: application/jsonl

{"id": "1", "title": "First"}
{"id": "2"}

### QUERY method (OpenAPI 3.2) with a request body

QUERY http://localhost:2000/documents
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "term": "membrane"
}

### in: querystring (OpenAPI 3.2) — the whole query string is typed, should work

GET http://localhost:2000/find?term=membrane&page=2

### in: querystring missing the required "term", should fail

GET http://localhost:2000/find?page=2

### xml.nodeType (OpenAPI 3.2) — id/currency as attributes, total as text, should work

POST http://localhost:2000/orders
Content-Type: application/xml

<order id="A1"><total currency="USD">42.5</total></order>

### xml.nodeType — total text is not a number, should fail

POST http://localhost:2000/orders
Content-Type: application/xml

<order id="A1"><total currency="USD">not-a-number</total></order>
